@startuml tunnel-inspect
title undef-terminal-tunnel — HTTP Inspect / Intercept Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam defaultFontColor #333333
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #2563eb
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #d1d5db
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #f3f4f6
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #d1d5db
skinparam noteBorderColor #d1d5db
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #f9fafb

participant "CLI Proxy\n(http_proxy.py)" as CLI
participant "Tunnel WS\n(client.py)" as TWS
participant "Server\n(fastapi_routes.py)" as SRV
participant "InterceptGate\n(intercept.py)" as GATE
participant "Browser\n(inspect-view.ts)" as UI

note over TWS
  Binary protocol per frame:
  [1B channel][1B flags][N payload]
  0x00=control  0x01=terminal
  0x02=TCP      0x03=HTTP
end note

== HTTP Request Captured ==

CLI -> TWS : CHANNEL_HTTP frame\n(request JSON)
TWS -> SRV : WS binary message
SRV -> GATE : enqueue request
GATE -> UI : push to inspect queue

alt Intercept Mode (gate open)
  UI -> GATE : action: forward / drop / modify
  GATE -> SRV : resolved action
  SRV -> TWS : CHANNEL_HTTP response frame
  TWS -> CLI : forward / drop result
else Passthrough Mode (gate closed)
  GATE -> SRV : auto-forward
  SRV -> TWS : CHANNEL_HTTP response frame
  TWS -> CLI : response bytes
end

== Terminal I/O (concurrent) ==

CLI -> TWS : CHANNEL_TERMINAL frame\n(PTY bytes)
TWS -> SRV : terminal data
SRV -> UI : xterm.js render

note over GATE
  InterceptGate actions:
  - forward: pass request unchanged
  - drop: discard silently
  - modify: rewrite headers/body
  Each pending request has a TTL.
end note

@enduml
